===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Something (usually [[money]]) given in [[exchange]] for [[influence]] or as an [[inducement]] to [[dishonesty]].
#* '''c. 1613-1625''', {{w|Sir Henry Hobart, 1st Baronet|Henry Hobart}}, ''Yardly v. Ellill''
#*: Undue reward for anything against justice is a '''bribe'''.
# That which seduces; [[seduction]]; [[allurement]].
#* '''1744''', {{w|Mark Akenside}}, ''{{w|The Pleasures of the Imagination}}''
#*: Not the '''bribes''' of sordid wealth can seduce to leave these everblooming sweets.
#* '''1974''', George Fox, {{w|Mario Puzo}}, ''[[w:Earthquake (film)|Earthquake]]''
#*: Remy, this was a '''bribe'''! Our whole marriage has been nothing but a series of bribes!

