#:{{ux|en|She was accused of trying to '''bribe''' the jury into making false statements.}}
#* '''October 23, 1848''', {{w|Frederick William Robertson}}, ''an address delivered at the Opening of The Working Men's Institute''
#*: Neither is he worthy who '''bribes''' a man to vote against his conscience.
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To gain by a bribe; to induce as by a bribe.
#: {{ux|en|to '''bribe''' somebody's compliance}}

